#### create database ---> via laravel


==> create migration files ? =-> php files  ---> write the structure you need to create in the database


### php artisan
php artisan make:migrations migration
new file created in database/migrations

--in the migration file ?

up() ---> calling when you run the migration

down() ---> calling when you rollback the migration

### target - -> create table products

php artisan make:migration create_products_table
https://laravel.com/docs/10.x/migrations

available columns datatypes
https://laravel.com/docs/10.x/migrations#available-column-types
### not that in the table created via migration files
the default of the columns is not null

